cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning systems to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the impact of feature selection on the security of machine learning systems, which is relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CR, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SI.
